The National Association of University Students (NAUS) on Sunday called on the Inspector- General of Police (IGP), Usman Alkali Baba to immediately withdraw police operatives attached to VIPs and deploy them to various institutions of learning across the country. The National President of the association, Ijegalu Felix, who stated this in Abeokuta, Ogun State, also lamented the incessant attacks on University campuses across the country by bandits, saying students now live in constant fear of being kidnapped or worst still, killed in a bid to be educated. 